Rating: 4
These cookies are AMAZING. I make them often and my friends at work always ask for more. Here are my two modifications: Reduce the oatmeal by 1/2 cup for a slightly chewier cookie. Be very sure not to overcook these--I recommend practically undercooking them. Remove from the oven just as the edges are starting to brown and the centers have just set. Then, let them sit in the pan for a full five minutes before removing them to cool--otherwise you'll have problems getting them onto the rack without them collapsing. This produces an extremly chewy cookie.

