I've made these cookies twice, and both times, I've...ahem...goofed up a bit. The first time, I forgot to add the baking soda to the dry ingredients, and had to mix it into the otherwise-finished dough. The second time, I made sure I added the baking soda to the flour and spices, and then forgot to add that whole bowl of dry stuff to the dough (sigh, don't ask!). Both times, I caught my mistake and fixed it before baking the cookies, and in both cases, the cookies came out wonderful! I consider these fool-proof. The first time, I used 3/4 cup of each type of sugar, and I think I prefer this. The second time, I used a full cup of each. One time, I used no cumin; the other time, just a tiny pinch. They were fine both ways, but I'm not eager to try it with the full or even half amount of cumin. These cookies are really addictive!

